chunk_content: When a patient has missed their most recent expected clinical contact, the clinic or other related staff should attempt to reach and reengage the patient as soon as possible. Once a PLHIV has reached 28 154 days past their expected clinical contact or drug pick-up, she/he/they should be removed from TX_CURR, the clinic should again attempt to reach and re-engage the patient, and her/his/their current outcome should be determined. The outcomes are defined as not currently on ART at the T R facility if the patient: E 1. Died A 2. Interruption in treatment (IIT) T M a. On treatment for <3 months when experienced IIT E b. On treatment for 3-5 months when experienced IIT N c. On treatment for 6+ months when experienced IIT T 3. Transferred out 4. Refused (stopped) treatment See Disaggregates and Descriptions section below for definitions of each of these outcomes.
